\f0\fs32 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Gutenberg is WordPress's core block editor for creating content layouts, while Full Site Editing (FSE) is a feature that uses Gutenberg blocks to customize an entire theme, including headers, footers, and templates
\f1 . ACF (Advanced Custom Fields) is a plugin that adds custom fields to WordPress, allowing developers to create specific data structures and is often used to build advanced Gutenberg blocks for more complex content. The key difference is scope: \cf3 Gutenberg is for content, FSE is for the whole site, and ACF is a tool for creating flexible custom content fields\cf2 .\'a0\
\
