\fs40 \cf2 Advanced Custom Fields (ACF)\'a0\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\fs32 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
What it is: A plugin that lets you add custom fields to posts, pages, and other post types.\
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Primary function: Adding structured, custom data fields to content.\
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
How it works: Creates custom fields (e.g., text, images, repeaters) that can be used in templates or built into Gutenberg blocks using ACF Blocks. ACF blocks are not native Gutenberg blocks but a way to build them more quickly, according to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://discourse.roots.io/t/transitioning-from-acf-flexible-content-to-gutenberg-acf-composer/29005"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 Roots Discourse}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://kanopi.com/blog/building-gutenberg-blocks-with-acf/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 Kanopi Studios}}.\
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Use case: Creating custom data entry for specific content types, providing developers with more control and making it easier for clients to input specific information.\'a0}